The euro declined versus the dollar
after European Central Bank President  Mario Draghi  said the
central bank is considering further non-standard monetary policy
tools and will deploy them if circumstances warrant.  The euro dropped 0.3 percent to $1.3329 at 7:19 a.m. London
time. The 17-nation currency pared an advance versus the yen to
trade 0.1 percent stronger at 126.45.  To contact the reporter on this story:
